Once a Kenilworth card-topper, the race ended up being incorporated into Met day in the modern trend to pack all racing’s jewels into a limited number of razzmatazz social race days. However, it was felt that this programming denied some progressive young horses a crack at both the Met and the Derby in the same year – especially after three-year-olds broke the one-time Met hoodoo for their age group. So, this year, the Cape Derby has been scheduled for 22 February – allowing for the “golden” rest period of three weeks after the Sun Met. But, best-laid plans and all...